# Why Can't We Be Like North Korea?
## For people who lay claim to a fervent patriotism, many restrictionists seem to really admire the immigration policies of other countries. Until they learn about them.

>**_The Short Stuff:_** When proposing immigration policies, it's tempting to point to those used by other nations as examples
of what the United States should do. Sometimes these comparisons are appropriate and interesting analogues. Other times, they are a horrific 
abandonment of the best of American values.


